One problem I have with casters in general is agro especially when people have the badly mistaken idea that their expience bar matters in a raid setting. This is what happens in a raid setting when a caster overnukes...<br>
<br>
All the rogues loss the chance to backstab until everyone repositions, this cuts their dmg by around 30%.<br>
<br>
All melees lose several rounds of melee while people find the mob and engage again.<br>
<br>
The MA loses taunt and more importantly can no longer hit the mob till he finds it and engages it again resulting in even less agro on him and even more chance of the next nuke by anyone sending the mob running around after the caster.<br>
<br>
Basicly overagroing as a caster can be like casting an AE slow on your entire raid. It's my impression that bad ping pong in a large group of people fighting player sized mobs cuts my dmg by at least 50-60%. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I will admit it I have done this in a Raid setting.  With the exception of pinging the mob.  I have a real problem being on a 8 hour raid going after yet another melee weapon.  And not seeing exp at least, one an hour.  I have NEVER seen a melee switch weapons so that exp could be spread arcoss multi-groups on a raid.  Not every fight on a raid is a life and death situation.<br>
<br>
I am in a guild that raids every night.  I am very familar with the way a raid works.  Since we raid every night our Tanks, and Healers are leveling a lot faster than the rest of us esspecially the wizards.  Our wizards level 2-3 times slower than any Tank class.  The only way our Wizards/ Mages/ Necros level is through soloing. &lt;Yawn&gt;<br>
