<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessage?topicID=603.topic">pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffe...=603.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
I do not have data points for the various melee classes at all levels or equipment levels. What I did do is take values from logs of rogues at 51, 58, 59, and 60, and do a linear interpolation to cover the ranges where I did not have actual data (including most of the levels pre-50). At 60, I used 100dps, which is lower than some of the rogues on Safehouse are claiming, but was the value I measured with Benton, a 60 rogue from Triton while we were doing the Myconoid King camp. In order to account for haste, I cut this value by half, giving a raw dps of 50. I then added an estimate for proc damage at 8 dps at 60 (proc dmg estimate is 3 dps for 55-59). This gives an unaccelerated raw dps of 58 for a 60 rogue. Adding 100% haste (item + buffs) then doubles this to 116 dps. Again, this is lower than what some rogues have been claiming on Safehouse, but if anything my proc damage estimate is on the high side.<br>
<br>
